spanishExample: De veras, me puede gustar.
englishTranslation: Really, I might like it.

spanishExample: De veras, no le importa.
englishTranslation: Really, It doesn’t matter to her.

spanishExample: En primer lugar, tengo cinco, no siete.
englishTranslation: In the first place, I have five, not seven.

spanishExample: Le gusto.
englishTranslation: She likes me.

spanishExample: Le importas porque eres seguro de ti mismo.
englishTranslation: You matter to her because you’re sure of yourself(m).

spanishExample: Les gusta la música, pero no les gustan esas cosas.
englishTranslation: They like music, but they don’t like those things.

spanishExample: Les importas y tienes que estar ahí a las seis en punto.
englishTranslation: You matter to them and you have to be there at six o’clock.

spanishExample: Me da igual, no le gustas.
englishTranslation: It’s all the same to me, she doesn’t like you.

spanishExample: Mi recuerdo de eso es que le gustas.
englishTranslation: My memory of that is that she likes you.

spanishExample: No importa, no es tu culpa.
englishTranslation: It doesn’t matter, it’s not your fault.

spanishExample: No le gustamos y tienes que darte cuenta de eso.
englishTranslation: She doesn’t like us and you have to realize that.

spanishExample: No le gusto, pero no le tengo que gustar.
englishTranslation: She doesn’t like me, but she doesn’t have to like me.

spanishExample: No le importan esas cosas.
englishTranslation: She doesn’t care about those things.

spanishExample: No le importan las cuentas.
englishTranslation: She doesn’t care about the accounts.

spanishExample: No le importo porque no le gusto.
englishTranslation: She doesn’t care about me because she doesn’t like me.

spanishExample: No les importamos porque somos seis.
englishTranslation: We don’t matter to them because we are six (people).

spanishExample: No me gusta cuando hablan entre sí.
englishTranslation: I don’t like it when they talk among themselves.

spanishExample: No me gusta esa casa, pero me gustan esos autos.
englishTranslation: I don’t like that house, but I like those cars.

spanishExample: Puede ser que tenga siete palabras.
englishTranslation: It might be that it has seven words.

spanishExample: Son las cinco en punto y nos tiene que importar.
englishTranslation: It’s five o’clock and it has to matter to us.

spanishExample: Te tiene que importar.
englishTranslation: It has to matter to you.

spanishExample: Tiene que darse cuenta de que hay cuatro personas aquí.
englishTranslation: She has to realize that there are four people here.

spanishExample: Tienes que hacer de cuenta que te gustan los cuatro.
englishTranslation: You have to pretend that you like all four.

spanishExample: Tienes que hacer de cuenta que te importa.
englishTranslation: You have to pretend that it matters to you.

spanishExample: Tu plan no tiene sentido.
englishTranslation: Your plan doesn’t make sense.
